                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.512351 Double/237: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marriner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-29T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 29, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 29—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>264. My 260, March 28, 1 p.m. I saw Foreign Minister Laval this morning who
                    informed me that the double taxation treaty passed the Senate last night. This
                    means that only the formalities of Presidential signature and exchange of
                    ratifications remain to be completed. Presumably the instrument of ratification
                    will be submitted to the President of the French Republic for his signature at
                    one of the Cabinet meetings next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marriner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
